					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12635244#post-4389852</guid>
				<title>Junior Staff - Site Criticism</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12635244/scp-4508#post-4389852</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 06 Oct 2019 12:28:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tanhony</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>776854</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I enjoyed this!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Tanhony&nbsp;rambles</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">TURN&nbsp;IT&nbsp;OFF</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>Just a few things that jumped out at me:</p> <blockquote> <p>The Parazoology Division sends patrols to the area of discovery on a monthly basis. Any otter populations will be observed and contained if necessary.</p> </blockquote> <p>Containment procedures are always the best hooks, in my opinion, and these lines work excellently for that purpose. They contrast wonderfully with the previous description of the items physical containment, and they hint at the otterocious events that are to come.</p> <blockquote> <p>The lucidity of SCP-4508-1 is currently unknown.</p> </blockquote> <p>Coming back to this after reading the entire SCP is just chilling, and it’s a good example of horror that works not only on the first read, but even better on subsequent ones.</p> <blockquote> <p>I hit a weird looking dog or somethign, idfk what it was… dead now</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>Had weirdest fucking dream. Got attacked by seals or some shit… when I woke up my room was a mess. W E I R D</p> </blockquote> <p>The inability to identify the animals as otters as first is a nice bit of comic relief, and it also helps us chart how Thomas begins taking the situation more seriously when he accurately identifies them. Nice inclusion!</p> <blockquote> <p>12:17pm|Rich: s p o o k y</p> </blockquote> <p>The tone in these text exchanges is very nice - I can picture this as a conversation between me and one of my friends, only I would never get my life ruined by otters.</p> <blockquote> <p>help</p> </blockquote> <p>I didn’t think I could be scared of an otter, but the picture here manages to do it. Just the way it’s reaching out to the camera gives me chills. Very nice choice of images here.</p> <p>Overall, I really like this one. A wonderful mix of horror and humour that leaves the reader wondering just what the hell happened here, while following its own internal logic of vengeful otters.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>+1</p> <p><sub><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Opinions expressed in this review do not reflect the opinions of SCP Wiki staff as a whole. Please respond to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tanhony" >Tanhony</a></span> or contact the captain of the Site Criticism Team, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" >SoullessSingularity</a></span>, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.</sub></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
